The paper discusses the use of deep learning models for predicting soil moisture using satellite-based observations. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of long short-term memory models, which are commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing, falling under the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of accurately modeling soil moisture, which has implications in weather and climate models, falling under the cs.NE sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of uncertainty estimates in the deep learning models, which falls under the cs.SD sub-category.
